  "prompt": "I am a third year mu engineering student. I have one kt in semester 2 will I get grace?",
  "response": "Grace marks or leniency in academic policy differ significantly from one educational institution to another, and sometimes even between different departments within the same institution. The possibility of receiving grace for a failed subject (KT or \"Keep Term\") in your second semester would depend on the specific rules and regulations of your university or college.\n\nGenerally, policies around grace marks might relate to factors such as:\n\n1. **Overall Performance:** Your overall academic performance and grades in other subjects might be considered.\n2. **Attendance:** Your attendance record could play a role.\n3. **University Policies:** Some institutions have predefined policies for granting grace marks under certain conditions.\n4. **Reason for KT:** If there were extenuating circumstances such as health issues, these might be taken into account.\n5. **Retake Opportunities:** Many institutions offer opportunities to retake the exam or subject in subsequent semesters.\n\nTo get accurate information on whether you qualify for grace marks, it would be best to check the specific academic policies of your university or speak directly with your academic advisor, department head, or the examination office. They can provide detailed information based on your institution's policies and your individual academic record.",
